================================================================================
Third-party software interoperation & attribution
================================================================================

tMAVEN  (GPL-3.0)  — Verma, Ray, Bodick, Kinz-Thompson & Gonzalez (2024),
  Biophysical Journal 123(14):2179–2193, doi:10.1016/j.bpj.2024.01.022.
  Upstream: https://github.com/GonzalezBiophysicsLab/tmaven  (pinned commit
  10f4230b6d13c6d2ad67b05d801696b4a40eff4a).
  Tether DOES NOT vendor tMAVEN. It runs an *isolated tMAVEN sidecar* in its own
  conda environment (PyQt5 + numpy<2) and exchanges data over the SMD-HDF5 format
  (PRD §4.3). A future M9 signed installer that BUNDLES the sidecar ships tMAVEN's
  own GPL-3.0 license text alongside Tether's, and the SBOM lists the sidecar as a
  distinct, attributed component (PRD §12.1, §12.8, §9 M9).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Bundled reference data (redistributed under its own license)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

kinSoftChallenge simulated datasets  (CC-BY-4.0)  — Götz, Barth, Bohr, et al.,
  "A blind benchmark of analysis tools to infer kinetic rate constants from
  single-molecule FRET trajectories," Nature Communications 13:5402 (2022),
  doi:10.1038/s41467-022-33023-3. Data: Götz M & Schmid S, Zenodo
  doi:10.5281/zenodo.5701310 (CC-BY-4.0).
  Tether bundles a repacked slice of the three *simulated* datasets
  (sim_dataset_Fig2/3/4) as the gated-tier fixture
  tests/fixtures/large/kinsoft_sim.hdf5 (+ one raw trace,
  tests/fixtures/kinsoft_trace_sample.txt), used only as an M8 kinetics-validation
  oracle (PRD §8 NFR-VALID(c), §9 M8). These files are licensed CC-BY-4.0 (see
  LICENSES/CC-BY-4.0.txt and the REUSE.toml annotation), NOT GPL-3.0; attribution
  to Götz & Schmid travels with them. The MATLAB simulator from the same record is
  NOT vendored (PRD N2 — Tether ships no data simulator).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Algorithm references (read-only; never vendored or redistributed)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Deep-LASI  — Wanninger, Asadiatouei, Bohlen, Salem, Tinnefeld, Ploetz & Lamb
  (2023), Nature Communications 14:6564, doi:10.1038/s41467-023-42272-9.
  Tether's native movie→trace extraction and registration mirror the Deep-LASI
  algorithm specification (PRD Appendix E); no Deep-LASI source is included.

MASH-FRET  — Börner, Kowerko, Hadzic, König, Ritter & Sigel (2018),
  PLoS ONE 13(4):e0195277, doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0195277.
  Consulted as a simulation / methodology reference (PRD Appendix references);
  no MASH-FRET source is included.

SMD (Single-Molecule Dataset) format — Greenfeld, van de Meent, Pavlichin,
  Mabuchi, Wiggins, Gonzalez & Herschlag (2015), BMC Bioinformatics 16:3,
  doi:10.1186/s12859-014-0429-4. The .tether project store is an SMD superset
  (PRD §5.3).

